comment._content: Princess Eleonore Caroline Gasparine Louise Reuss of Köstritz (22 August 1860 – 12 September 1917) was Tsaritsa of Bulgaria and the second wife of Tsar Ferdinand of Bulgaria. Her name is borne of ancient Eastern European origin, meaning 'true and perpetual beauty'. en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eleonore_Reuss_of_K%C3%B6stritz
